This Is Really A Wild Place Up Here
<p>“In times of never-greater hype around the future of technological advancements, we go back to another tech revolution of the past. February 9th marks the day of Apollo 14’s landing on the moon, the third in NASA’s crewed space program. Our February calendar design aims to connect the tech endeavors of the present and past and serve as a reminder that innovation should always be used for a good cause.” — Designed by <a href="https://www.popwebdesign.net/ecommerce-development.html">PopArt Studio</a> from Serbia.</p>
